While the app is great, I sometimes felt that the daily prompts and reminders were too general and not tailored enough to my specific needs or goals. Adding more personalized features, like adapting content based on user preferences or feedback, would make it even more engaging and relevant. I’d also love to see a better integration of community support, maybe a feature for connecting with others who are working on similar goals.
column122: Absolutely, I think it would be useful for universities to offer the Flourish app as a wellness tool. College life can be stressful, and having an accessible, user-friendly app focused on mindfulness, goal-setting, and emotional well-being could make a real difference for students. The app could be particularly helpful for students who might not feel comfortable seeking in-person counseling or who need a supplementary tool to manage stress. By offering it through the university, it could also signal a stronger commitment to supporting student wellness, which is so important in today’s fast-paced academic environment.
